h8501.definition: from an unused root meaning; to dissever, i.e. crush; deceitful.

h8503.definition: from {{h3615}}; completion; by implication, an extremity; end, perfect(-ion).

h8504.definition: probably for {{h7827}}; the cerulean mussel, i.e. the color (violet) obtained therefrom or stuff dyed therewith; blue.

h8505.definition: a primitive root; to balance, i.e. measure out (by weight or dimension); figuratively to arrange, equalize, through the idea of levelling (ment, estimate, test); bear up, direct, be (un-)equal, mete, ponder, tell, weigh.

h8506.definition: from {{h8505}}; a fixed quantity; measure, tale.

h8507.definition: the same as {{h8506}}; Token, a place in Palestine; Tochen.

h8508.definition: from {{h8506}}; admeasurement, i.e. consummation; pattern, sum.

h8509.definition: apparently from an unused root meaning to encompass; a wrapper or robe; garment.

h8510.definition: by contraction from {{h8524}}; a mound; heap, × strength.

h8511.definition: a primitive root; to suspend; figuratively (through hesitation) to be uncertain; by implication (of mental dependence) to habituate; be bent, hang (in doubt).

h8512.definition: from {{h8510}} and {{h24}}; mound of green growth; Tel-Abib, a place in Chaldaea; Tel-abib.

h8515.definition: or תְּלַשַּׂר; of foreign derivation; Telassar, a region of Assyria; Telassar.

h8518.definition: a primitive root; to suspend (especially to gibbet); hang (up).

h8519.definition: or תּלֻנָּה; from {{h3885}} in the sense of obstinacy; a grumbling; murmuring.

h8520.definition: probably from an unused root meaning to dissever; breach; Telach, an Israelite; Telah.

h8521.definition: from {{h8510}} and the feminine of {{h2798}}; mound of workmanship; Tel-Charsha, a place in Babylonia; Tel-haresha, Tel-harsa.

h8522.definition: probably from {{h8518}}; a quiver (as slung); quiver.

h8523.definition: (Aramaic) or תַּלְתִּי; (Aramaic), ordinal from {{h8532}}; third; third.

h8524.definition: a primitive root; to pile up, i.e. elevate; eminent. Compare {{h2048}}.

h8525.definition: from an unused root meaning to accumulate; a bank or terrace; furrow, ridge.

h8526.definition: from {{h8525}}; ridged; Talmai, the name of a Canaanite and a Syrian; Talmai.

h8528.definition: from {{h8510}} and {{h4417}}; mound of salt; Tel-Melach, a place in Babylonia; Tel-melah.

h8529.definition: a denominative from {{h8438}}; to crimson, i.e. dye that color; × scarlet.

h8530.definition: feminine from an unused root meaning to tower; something tall, i.e. (plural collective) slenderness; armoury.

h8532.definition: (Aramaic) masculine תְּלָתָה; (Aramaic), or תְּלָתָא; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h7969}}; three or third; third, three.

h8533.definition: (Aramaic) multiple of {{h8532}}; ten times three; thirty.

h8534.definition: by reduplication, from {{h8524}} through the idea of vibration; a trailing bough (as pendulous); bushy.

h8535.definition: from {{h8552}}; complete; usually (morally) pious; specifically, gentle, dear; coupled together, perfect, plain, undefiled, upright.

h8536.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h8033}}; there; × thence, there, × where.

h8537.definition: from {{h8552}}; completeness; figuratively, prosperity; usually (morally) innocence; full, integrity, perfect(-ion), simplicity, upright(-ly, -ness), at a venture. See {{h8550}}.

h8539.definition: a primitive root; to be in consternation; be amazed, be astonished, marvel(-lously), wonder.

h8540.definition: (Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h8539}}; a miracle; wonder.

h8542.definition: of uncertain derivation; Tammuz, a Phoenician deity; Tammuz.

h8543.definition: or תְּמֹל; probably for {{h865}}; sometimes with	{{h8032}}; properly, ago, i.e. a (short or long) time since; especially yesterday, or day before yesterday; before (-time),   these (three) days,   heretofore,   time past, yesterday.

h8544.definition: or תְּמֻנָה; from {{h4327}}; something portioned (i.e. fashioned) out, as a shape, i.e. (indefinitely) phantom, or (specifically) embodiment, or (figuratively) manifestation (of favor); image, likeness, similitude.

h8545.definition: from {{h4171}}; barter, compensation; (ex-) change(-ing), recompense, restitution.

h8546.definition: from {{h4191}}; execution (as a doom); death, die.

h8547.definition: of uncertain derivation; Temach, one of the Nethinim; Tamah, Thamah.

h8548.definition: from an unused root meaning to stretch; properly, continuance (as indefinite extension); but used only (attributively as adjective) constant (or adverbially, constantly); elliptically the regular (daily) sacrifice; alway(-s), continual (employment, -ly), daily, (n-)ever(-more), perpetual.

h8549.definition: from {{h8552}}; entire (literally, figuratively or morally); also (as noun) integrity, truth; without blemish, complete, full, perfect, sincerely (-ity), sound, without spot, undefiled, upright(-ly), whole.

h8550.definition: plural of {{h8537}}; perfections, i.e. (techn.) one of the epithets of the objects in the high-priest's breastplate as an emblem of complete Truth; Thummim.

h8551.definition: a primitive root; to sustain; by implication, to obtain, keep fast; figuratively, to help, follow close; (take, up-) hold (up), maintain, retain, stay (up).

h8552.definition: a primitive root; to complete, in a good or a bad sense, literal, or figurative, transitive or intransitive; accomplish, cease, be clean (pass-) ed, consume, have done, (come to an, have an, make an) end, fail, come to the full, be all gone, × be all here, be (make) perfect, be spent, sum, be (shew self) upright, be wasted, whole.

h8553.definition: from {{h4487}}; a portion assigned; Timnah, the name of two places in Palestine; Timnah, Timnath, Thimnathah.

h8554.definition: patrial from {{h8553}}; a Timnite or inhabitant of Timnah; Timnite.

h8555.definition: from {{h4513}}; restraint; Timna, the name of two Edomites; Timna, Timnah.

h8556.definition: or תִּמְנַת סֶרַח; from {{h8553}} and {{h2775}}; portion of (the) sun; Timnath-Cheres, a place in Palestine; Timnath-heres, Timnath-serah.

h8558.definition: from an unused root meaning to be erect; a palm tree; palm (tree).

h8559.definition: the same as {{h8558}}; Tamar, the name of three women and a place; Tamar.

h8560.definition: from the same root as {{h8558}}; a palm trunk; palm tree.

h8561.definition: (plural or (feminine) תִּמֹּרָה; (singular and plural), from the same root as {{h8558}}; (architectural) a palm-like pilaster (i.e. umbellate); palm tree.

h8562.definition: or תַּמְרֻק; or תַּמְרִיק; from {{h4838}}; properly, a scouring, i.e. soap or perfumery for the bath; figuratively, a detergent; × cleanse, (thing for) purification(-fying).

h8563.definition: from {{h4843}}; bitterness (plural as collective); × most bitter(-ly).

h8564.definition: from the same root as {{h8558}}; an erection, i.e. pillar (probably for a guide-board); high heap.

h8565.definition: from an unused root probably meaning to elongate; a monster (as preternaturally formed), i.e. a sea-serpent (or other huge marine animal); also a jackal (or other hideous land animal); dragon, whale. Compare {{h8577}}.

h8566.definition: a primitive root; to present (a mercenary inducement), i.e. bargain with (a harlot); hire.

h8567.definition: a primitive root (identical with through the idea of attributing honor); to ascribe (praise), i.e. celebrate, commemorate; lament, rehearse.

h8568.definition: probably feminine of {{h8565}}; a female jackal; dragon.

h8569.definition: from {{h5106}}; alienation; by implication, enmity; breach of promise, occasion.

h8571.definition: perhaps from the same as {{h594}} through the idea of protraction; a pinnacle, i.e. extremity; tip.

h8573.definition: from {{h5130}}; a brandishing (in threat); by implication, tumult; specifically, the official undulation of sacrificial offerings; offering, shaking, wave (offering).

h8575.definition: or תַּנְחֻם; and (feminine) תַּנְחוּמָה; from {{h5162}}; compassion, solace; comfort, consolation.

h8577.definition: or תַּנִּים; (Ezekiel 29:3), intensive from the same as {{h8565}}; a marine or land monster, i.e. sea-serpent or jackal; dragon, sea-monster, serpent, whale.

h8580.definition: from {{h5395}}; properly, a hard breather, i.e. the name of two unclean creatures, a lizard and a bird (both perhaps from changing color through their irascibility), probably the tree-toad and the water-hen; mole, swan.

h8581.definition: a primitive root; to loathe, i.e. (morally) detest; (make to be) abhor(-red), (be, commit more, do) abominable(-y), × utterly.

h8582.definition: a primitive root; to vacillate, i.e. reel or stray (literally or figuratively); also causative of both; (cause to) go astray, deceive, dissemble, (cause to, make to) err, pant, seduce, (make to) stagger, (cause to) wander, be out of the way.

h8583.definition: or תֹּעִי; from {{h8582}}; error; Tou or Toi, a Syrian king; Toi, Tou.

h8584.definition: from {{h5749}}; attestation, i.e. a precept, usage; testimony.

h8585.definition: from {{h5927}}; a channel (into which water is raised for irrigation); also a bandage or plaster (as placed upon a wound); conduit, cured, healing, little river, trench, watercourse.

h8586.definition: from {{h5953}}; caprice (as a fit coming on), i.e. vexation; concretely a tyrant; babe, delusion.

h8587.definition: from {{h5956}}; a secret; thing that is hid, secret.

h8588.definition: or תַּעֲנֻג; and (feminine) תַּעֲנֻגָה; from {{h6026}}; luxury; delicate, delight, pleasant.

h8589.definition: from {{h6031}}; affliction (of self), i.e. fasting; heaviness.

h8590.definition: or תַּעְנָךְ; of uncertain derivation; Taanak or Tanak, a place in Palestine; Taanach, Tanach.

h8591.definition: a primitive root; to cheat; by analogy, to maltreat; deceive, misuse.

h8593.definition: from {{h6168}}; a knife or razor (as making bare); also a scabbard (as being bare, i.e. empty); (pen-) knife, razor, scabbard, shave, sheath.

h8594.definition: from {{h6148}}; suretyship, i.e. (concretely) a pledge; hostage.

h8596.definition: from {{h8608}} contracted; a tambourine; tabret, timbrel.

h8597.definition: or תִּפְאֶרֶת; from {{h6286}}; ornament (abstractly or concretely, literally or figuratively); beauty(-iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), honour, majesty.

h8598.definition: from {{h5301}}; an apple (from its fragrance), i.e. the fruit or the tree (probably includ. others of the pome order, as the quince, the orange, etc.); apple (tree). See also {{h1054}}.

h8599.definition: the same as {{h8598}}; Tappuach, the name of two places in Palestine, also of an Israelite; Tappuah.
